49////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
50// Merge
51
52PARAM_TEST_CASE(Merge, cv::gpu::DeviceInfo, cv::Size, MatDepth, Channels, UseRoi)
53{
54 cv::gpu::DeviceInfo devInfo;
55 cv::Size size;
56 int depth;
57 int channels;
58 bool useRoi;
59
60 virtual void SetUp()
61 {
62 devInfo = GET_PARAM(0);
63 size = GET_PARAM(1);
64 depth = GET_PARAM(2);
65 channels = GET_PARAM(3);
66 useRoi = GET_PARAM(4);
67
68 cv::gpu::setDevice(devInfo.deviceID());
69 }
70};
71
72GPU_TEST_P(Merge, Accuracy)
73{
74 std::vector<cv::Mat> src;
75 src.reserve(channels);
76 for (int i = 0; i < channels; ++i)
77 src.push_back(cv::Mat(size, depth, cv::Scalar::all(i)));
78
79 std::vector<cv::gpu::GpuMat> d_src;
80 for (int i = 0; i < channels; ++i)
81 d_src.push_back(loadMat(src[i], useRoi));
82
83 if (depth == CV_64F && !supportFeature(devInfo, cv::gpu::NATIVE_DOUBLE))
84 {
85 try
86 {
87 cv::gpu::GpuMat dst;
88 cv::gpu::merge(d_src, dst);
89 }
90 catch (const cv::Exception& e)
91 {
92 ASSERT_EQ(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, e.code);
93 }
94 }
95 else
96 {
97 cv::gpu::GpuMat dst;
98 cv::gpu::merge(d_src, dst);
99
100 cv::Mat dst_gold;
101 cv::merge(src, dst_gold);
102
103 EXPECT_MAT_NEAR(dst_gold, dst, 0.0);
104 }
105}
106
107INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(GPU_Core, Merge, testing::Combine(
108 ALL_DEVICES,
109 DIFFERENT_SIZES,
110 ALL_DEPTH,
111 testing::Values(1, 2, 3, 4),
112 WHOLE_SUBMAT));
113

117PARAM_TEST_CASE(Split, cv::gpu::DeviceInfo, cv::Size, MatDepth, Channels, UseRoi)
118{
119 cv::gpu::DeviceInfo devInfo;
120 cv::Size size;
121 int depth;
122 int channels;
123 bool useRoi;
124
125 int type;
126
127 virtual void SetUp()
128 {
129 devInfo = GET_PARAM(0);
130 size = GET_PARAM(1);
131 depth = GET_PARAM(2);
132 channels = GET_PARAM(3);
133 useRoi = GET_PARAM(4);
134
135 cv::gpu::setDevice(devInfo.deviceID());
136
137 type = CV_MAKE_TYPE(depth, channels);
138 }
139};
140
141GPU_TEST_P(Split, Accuracy)
142{
143 cv::Mat src = randomMat(size, type);
144
145 if (depth == CV_64F && !supportFeature(devInfo, cv::gpu::NATIVE_DOUBLE))
146 {
147 try
148 {
149 std::vector<cv::gpu::GpuMat> dst;
150 cv::gpu::split(loadMat(src), dst);
151 }
152 catch (const cv::Exception& e)
153 {
154 ASSERT_EQ(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, e.code);
155 }
156 }
157 else
158 {
159 std::vector<cv::gpu::GpuMat> dst;
160 cv::gpu::split(loadMat(src, useRoi), dst);
161
162 std::vector<cv::Mat> dst_gold;
163 cv::split(src, dst_gold);
164
165 ASSERT_EQ(dst_gold.size(), dst.size());
166
167 for (size_t i = 0; i < dst_gold.size(); ++i)
168 {
169 EXPECT_MAT_NEAR(dst_gold[i], dst[i], 0.0);
170 }
171 }
172}
173
174INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(GPU_Core, Split, testing::Combine(
175 ALL_DEVICES,
176 DIFFERENT_SIZES,
177 ALL_DEPTH,
178 testing::Values(1, 2, 3, 4),
179 WHOLE_SUBMAT));

184PARAM_TEST_CASE(Add_Array, cv::gpu::DeviceInfo, cv::Size, std::pair<MatDepth, MatDepth>, Channels, UseRoi)
185{
186 cv::gpu::DeviceInfo devInfo;
187 cv::Size size;
188 std::pair<MatDepth, MatDepth> depth;
189 int channels;
190 bool useRoi;
191
192 int stype;
193 int dtype;
194
195 virtual void SetUp()
196 {
197 devInfo = GET_PARAM(0);
198 size = GET_PARAM(1);
199 depth = GET_PARAM(2);
200 channels = GET_PARAM(3);
201 useRoi = GET_PARAM(4);
202
203 cv::gpu::setDevice(devInfo.deviceID());
204
205 stype = CV_MAKE_TYPE(depth.first, channels);
206 dtype = CV_MAKE_TYPE(depth.second, channels);
207 }
208};
209
210GPU_TEST_P(Add_Array, Accuracy)
211{
212 cv::Mat mat1 = randomMat(size, stype);
213 cv::Mat mat2 = randomMat(size, stype);
214
215 if ((depth.first == CV_64F || depth.second == CV_64F) && !supportFeature(devInfo, cv::gpu::NATIVE_DOUBLE))
216 {
217 try
218 {
219 cv::gpu::GpuMat dst;
220 cv::gpu::add(loadMat(mat1), loadMat(mat2), dst, cv::gpu::GpuMat(), depth.second);
221 }
222 catch (const cv::Exception& e)
223 {
224 ASSERT_EQ(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, e.code);
225 }
226 }
227 else
228 {
229 cv::gpu::GpuMat dst = createMat(size, dtype, useRoi);
230 dst.setTo(cv::Scalar::all(0));
231 cv::gpu::add(loadMat(mat1, useRoi), loadMat(mat2, useRoi), dst, cv::gpu::GpuMat(), depth.second);
232
233 cv::Mat dst_gold(size, dtype, cv::Scalar::all(0));
234 cv::add(mat1, mat2, dst_gold, cv::noArray(), depth.second);
235
236 EXPECT_MAT_NEAR(dst_gold, dst, depth.first >= CV_32F || depth.second >= CV_32F ? 1e-4 : 0.0);
237 }
238}

1714////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1715// Compare_Scalar
1716
1717namespace
1718{
1719 template <template <typename> class Op, typename T>
1720 void compareScalarImpl(const cv::Mat& src, cv::Scalar sc, cv::Mat& dst)
1721 {
1722 Op<T> op;
1723
1724 const int cn = src.channels();
1725
1726 dst.create(src.size(), CV_MAKE_TYPE(CV_8U, cn));
1727
1728 for (int y = 0; y < src.rows; ++y)
1729 {
1730 for (int x = 0; x < src.cols; ++x)
1731 {
1732 for (int c = 0; c < cn; ++c)
1733 {
1734 T src_val = src.at<T>(y, x * cn + c);
1735 T sc_val = cv::saturate_cast<T>(sc.val[c]);
1736 dst.at<uchar>(y, x * cn + c) = static_cast<uchar>(static_cast<int>(op(src_val, sc_val)) * 255);
1737 }
1738 }
1739 }
1740 }
1741
1742 void compareScalarGold(const cv::Mat& src, cv::Scalar sc, cv::Mat& dst, int cmpop)
1743 {
1744 typedef void (*func_t)(const cv::Mat& src, cv::Scalar sc, cv::Mat& dst);
1745 static const func_t funcs[7][6] =
1746 {
1747 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, unsigned char> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, unsigned char> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, unsigned char> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, unsigned char> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, unsigned char> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, unsigned char> },
1748 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, signed char> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, signed char> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, signed char> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, signed char> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, signed char> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, signed char> },
1749 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, unsigned short>, compareScalarImpl<std::greater, unsigned short>, compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, unsigned short>, compareScalarImpl<std::less, unsigned short>, compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, unsigned short>, compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, unsigned short>},
1750 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, short> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, short> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, short> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, short> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, short> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, short> },
1751 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, int> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, int> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, int> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, int> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, int> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, int> },
1752 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, float> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, float> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, float> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, float> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, float> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, float> },
1753 {compareScalarImpl<std::equal_to, double> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater, double> , compareScalarImpl<std::greater_equal, double> , compareScalarImpl<std::less, double> , compareScalarImpl<std::less_equal, double> , compareScalarImpl<std::not_equal_to, double> }
1754 };
1755
1756 funcs[src.depth()][cmpop](src, sc, dst);
1757 }
1758}

3101// Sum

3103namespace
3104{
3105 template <typename T>
3106 cv::Scalar absSumImpl(const cv::Mat& src)
3107 {
3108 const int cn = src.channels();
3109
3110 cv::Scalar sum = cv::Scalar::all(0);
3111
3112 for (int y = 0; y < src.rows; ++y)
3113 {
3114 for (int x = 0; x < src.cols; ++x)
3115 {
3116 for (int c = 0; c < cn; ++c)
3117 sum[c] += std::abs(src.at<T>(y, x * cn + c));
3118 }
3119 }
3120
3121 return sum;
3122 }
3123
3124 cv::Scalar absSumGold(const cv::Mat& src)
3125 {
3126 typedef cv::Scalar (*func_t)(const cv::Mat& src);
3127
3128 static const func_t funcs[] =
3129 {
3130 absSumImpl<uchar>,
3131 absSumImpl<schar>,
3132 absSumImpl<ushort>,
3133 absSumImpl<short>,
3134 absSumImpl<int>,
3135 absSumImpl<float>,
3136 absSumImpl<double>
3137 };
3138
3139 return funcs[src.depth()](src);
3140 }
3141
3142 template <typename T>
3143 cv::Scalar sqrSumImpl(const cv::Mat& src)
3144 {
3145 const int cn = src.channels();
3146
3147 cv::Scalar sum = cv::Scalar::all(0);
3148
3149 for (int y = 0; y < src.rows; ++y)
3150 {
3151 for (int x = 0; x < src.cols; ++x)
3152 {
3153 for (int c = 0; c < cn; ++c)
3154 {
3155 const T val = src.at<T>(y, x * cn + c);
3156 sum[c] += val * val;
3157 }
3158 }
3159 }
3160
3161 return sum;
3162 }
3163
3164 cv::Scalar sqrSumGold(const cv::Mat& src)
3165 {
3166 typedef cv::Scalar (*func_t)(const cv::Mat& src);
3167
3168 static const func_t funcs[] =
3169 {
3170 sqrSumImpl<uchar>,
3171 sqrSumImpl<schar>,
3172 sqrSumImpl<ushort>,
3173 sqrSumImpl<short>,
3174 sqrSumImpl<int>,
3175 sqrSumImpl<float>,
3176 sqrSumImpl<double>
3177 };
3178
3179 return funcs[src.depth()](src);
3180 }

3373
3374 void expectEqual(const cv::Mat& src, cv::Point loc_gold, cv::Point loc)
3375 {
3376 typedef void (*func_t)(const cv::Mat& src, cv::Point loc_gold, cv::Point loc);
3377
3378 static const func_t funcs[] =
3379 {
3380 expectEqualImpl<uchar>,
3381 expectEqualImpl<schar>,
3382 expectEqualImpl<ushort>,
3383 expectEqualImpl<short>,
3384 expectEqualImpl<int>,
3385 expectEqualImpl<float>,
3386 expectEqualImpl<double>
3387 };
3388
3389 funcs[src.depth()](src, loc_gold, loc);
3390 }
3391}
